      <section eId="sec_CCP-2852">
        <num>CCP 2852</num>
        <heading>2852. Â Documents submitted with petition for probate</heading>
        <subsection eId="CCP-2852__subsec_A">
          <num>A.</num>
          <content>
            <p>The petitioner shall submit with his petition evidence of the death of the decedent, and of all other facts necessary to establish the jurisdiction of the court.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CCP-2852__subsec_B">
          <num>B.</num>
          <content>
            <p>If the testament is one other than a statutory testament, a notarial testament, or a nuncupative testament by public act, and is in the possession of the petitioner, he shall present it to the court, and pray that it be probated and executed.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=111549</p>
        </authorialNote>
      </section>
